beer.beer_name: The Dank - Imperial DDH West Coast IPA - Pilot Brew #2
beer.beer_description:
Pilot Brew #2

A fruit but sticky dank and bitter IPA a homage to the early west coast IPAs that inspired a new generation. Stone fruit, sticky pine with a biscuit sweet caramel malt profile balancing the 70 IBUs.

items.badge_description: Lovers of little green cones rejoice. National IPA Day is pretty much like your best birthday! Whether you love hazies, milkshake, double, triple, or even quad IPAs just check in one today to earn this coveted badge.

A global celebration of beer, International Beer Day toasts to beers from all across the globe. Like a helles from Germany, a tripel from Belgian, or an ESB from Britain. Cheers to you, wherever you might be in the world!
We believe in IPA and you should too. You certainly have a taste for the hops! That's 355 different IPAs. Try 5 more for Level 72! Want to learn more about this badge? Check out our podcast

items.badge_description: Fresh from the tap is one of the best ways to enjoy a beer. Just try to use a glass and not drink directly from the tap, as tempting as it may be. That's 30 checkins with the serving style of Draft. Try 5 more for Level 7!

Everyone loves fresh beer, but obviously not as much as you do. You went straight to the source. 

That's a beer at 5 different venues categorized as a Brewery, Cidery or Meadery. Visit 5 more for Level 2!
There is nothing quite like a dive bar with its cigarette smoke, ripped vinyl booths, and bar stools brimming with spilled beer and nostalgia. We all have our favorite dive bar. What's yours?
